                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3326: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-09T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 9, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>62. Your 41, April 8, 2 p.m. President Leguia is at a loss to know how the
                    American engineers’ report could have been answered April <pb facs="0897"
                        n="761" xml:id="pg_761"/> 4th by Chile when he did not deliver it to the
                    Chilean Ambassador here until April 6th.</p>
                <p>Engineer Seeley will today prepare an answer to the Chilean engineers’
                    statements.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
